e Frage aufgeworfen, ob - und wenn ja, inwiefern - die religionspolitischen Lernprozesse des europäischen, lateinchristlich geprägten Erfahrungsraumes auf andere Regionen und Religionen der Welt übertragen werden können.  aThis volume submits the principle of separation between religion and politics in modern democracies to an up-to-date evaluation. It shows that there are good reasons for it, which however are obscured by the purely metaphorical talk of »separation«.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aChurch and statezFrancexHistory. 0aChurch and statezGermanyxHistory. 0aChurch and statezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aDemocratizationzFrancexHistory. 0aDemocratizationzGermanyxHistory. 0aDemocratizationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aReligion and politicszFrancexHistory. 0aReligion and politicszGermanyxHistory. 0aReligion and politicszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aReligion and politics. 4aHabermas. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Philosophie. 4aPolitische Theorie. 4aReligion. 4aRousseau. 4aStaat. 4aSäkularismus. 4aTocqueville. 4aTrennung Von Staat und Kirche. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh  aHabermas.  aPolitical Philosophy.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aReligion.  aRousseau.  aSecularism.  aState.  aTocqueville.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2015 Part 2z978311076664608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z97831107009850 cprintz978383762965140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839429655?